        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued September 12 at 2:28PM MDT until September 12 at 3:00PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>SVRGJT

The National Weather Service in Grand Junction has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
West central Mesa County in west central Colorado...
East central Grand County in east central Utah...

* Until 300 PM MDT.

* At 228 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 23 miles southwest
of Fruita, or 27 miles southwest of Grand Junction, moving
northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Glade Park.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
